Former Senator and 2023 Kaduna Gubernatorial aspirant, Shehu Sani, has revealed the reason the ruling party, All Progressive Congress (APC), and the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) keep postponing their primary elections. According to the former lawmaker in a tweet on Saturday, both parties keep shifting the dates as they are the grandmasters of the political game with tricks up their sleeves. His tweet reads, “PDP and APC keep shifting dates; the Grandmasters of the game knows the tricks of each other.” -Advertisement-